values: So, you probably know that Chunking Express was brought to the US by Tarantino who was a big fan of Kar Wai's action HK flicks. Well, here is a deleted scene from In the Mood for Love (honestly, I think it was a crew gig rather than a planed scene... but know knows.....) and here is the real thing, a pure beauty of cinema All Kar Wai's "1960" trilogy in Castro Theater next Sat, the 16th. http://www.castrotheatre.com/p-list.html

World Cup is like Burning Man.  So much joy, so much fun, so much excitement!  There is always someone who complains that it used to be better, that art is not as good this year, that scoring is down, that referee and dust storms suck.  And all I say: so much joy, so much fun, so much excitement!  My grudge with BM?  I stopped watching the Burn some time ago.  But I am sooooo watching the final, oh, Dutch vs. Spain, can it get any better?!!!
July 9 - July 18, here we come again!
